Sec. 58.0177. APPOINTED MEMBER PREPARATION PROGRAM. The board
shall provide each appointed member of the board financial training
adequate to prepare the member for the responsibilities of board
membership before the member may begin service.
Added by Acts 1995, 74th Leg., ch. 419, Sec. 5.16, eff. Sept. 1,
1995.

SUBCHAPTER C. PURPOSES AND POWERS
